            "id": "4543987",
            "title": "Alibaba joins hands with China's Zelos for $2B robovan business - report",
            "description": "<html><body><ul>\n<li><span>Alibaba's (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/BABA\" title=\"Alibaba Group Holding Limited\">BABA</a></span>) logistics arm, Cainiao, is merging its autonomous-driving unit with China's Zelos Technology to form a new robovan business valued at around $2B, <em>The Wall Street Journal </em>reported, citing people familiar with the matter.</span></li>\n<li><span>Alibaba will gain an equity stake in Zelos Technology, while Cainiao Robovan will continue to operate as an individual brand after the merger.</span></li>\n<li><span>The merged entity will be run by Zelos, <span>and a Cainiao executive will join Zelos’s board, the people <a href=\"https://www.wsj.com/business/deals/alibaba-to-team-up-with-zelos-on-2-billion-robovan-business-8ed38b7e\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"said\">said</a>.</span> </span></li>\n<li><span>A formal deal announcement is expected by Thursday, the report added.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
